You will act as an evangelist for Energy Efficiency, driving synergies with Smart Grid Technologies, Distributed Energy Resources, and Electric Vehicle Charging Infrastructure. Additionally, you will stay current on industry trends, provide strategic insights, and contribute to new business development by developing solutions, managing workstreams, and leading client meetings and workshops. Your expertise will also be crucial in supporting business development activities, including go-to-market strategies, project management, and client relationship building. The role requires a deep understanding of the P&U lifecycle, extensive experience in sales enablement and program management, and a solid background in Smart Energy Solutions and Digital Utilities Transformation. The ideal candidate will possess a degree in Electrical Engineering, knowledge of power system modeling standards, and a minimum of 15 years of experience, with at least 10 years focused on the P&U sector. Strong communication, project management, and people management skills, along with a proactive, problem-solving mindset, are essential. This role offers a unique opportunity to shape the future of the P&U sector while working in a dynamic, globally recognized consulting environment.
